{:synth/id   :klank-bars
 :synth/tags [:physical-model :resonator :dyn-klank :marimba :vibraphone :pitched]
 :synth/doc  "Tuned resonator bar voice via DynKlank -- marimba/vibraphone character.

  Models the acoustic behaviour of a uniform stiff bar (marimba, vibraphone,
  xylophone, glockenspiel family). The partial structure of a stiff bar differs
  from a string or bell: the overtones follow the equation fn = f1 * (2n-1)^2 / 3,
  producing a near-harmonic but slightly stretched series.

  Default partial ratios (from Fletcher & Rossing, tuned bar analysis):
    f1: 1.000 x freq  -- fundamental (dominant, the perceived pitch)
    f2: 2.756 x freq  -- first overtone (slightly inharmonic, adds warmth)
    f3: 5.404 x freq  -- second overtone (bright, short decay)

  Note: the marimba/vibraphone maker uses bar undercuts to tune the first
  overtone to exactly 4x the fundamental (two octaves up), suppressing the
  intermediate partials. The default here is the uncut bar -- for marimba
  character, set :f2 to 4.0 and :a3/:d3 to very low values.

  For vibraphone character (longer, more singing decay):
    (sc/sc-play! {:synth :klank-bars :freq-scale 440 :d1 2.5 :d2 1.5 :d3 0.5})

  For xylophone character (harder, drier, short decay):
    (sc/sc-play! {:synth :klank-bars :freq-scale 880 :d1 0.2 :d2 0.1 :d3 0.05})

  For glockenspiel (bright, long-sustaining):
    (sc/sc-play! {:synth :klank-bars :freq-scale 2000 :d1 3.0 :d2 2.5 :d3 2.0})

  Excitation: a bandpass-filtered noise burst through a fast perc envelope.
  Wider :exc-bw (excitation bandwidth) gives a harder, brighter mallet attack.

  Primary arc targets: :freq-scale (retune), :d1/:d2/:d3 (decay sculpting)"
 :args  {:freq-scale 440.0
         :amp        0.65
         :f1 1.0     :a1 1.0    :d1 0.8
         :f2 2.756   :a2 0.45   :d2 0.4
         :f3 5.404   :a3 0.2    :d3 0.15
         :exc-bw     400.0
         :pan        0.0}
 :graph [:out 0
          [:pan2
           [:* :amp
               [:dyn-klank
                [:* 0.4 [:* [:env-gen [:perc 0.001 0.015] :gate 1.0]
                             [:bpf [:white-noise] :freq-scale :exc-bw]]]
                :freq-scale
                :f1 :a1 :d1
                :f2 :a2 :d2
                :f3 :a3 :d3]]
           :pan]]}
